<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4612303>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 11. Characteristics of synspermia and spermatozoa of Neotrops poguazu. A: Sperm conjugates are surrounded by a thin secretion sheath. B: The chromatin is irregularly condensed. C: The AF extends toward the nucleus and projects into the periphery of the nucleus, surrounded by the NC. D: Within the ejaculatory duct sperm conjugates further differentiate. This includes further condensation of cytoplasm while peripheral constrictions recess." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4612303/files/figure.png" .

