<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4612307>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 12. Characteristics of spermiogenesis of Neotrops poguazu. A: The small AV is bordered from the nucleus by a distinct electron-dense plate (magnified in inset). B: The chromatin starts condensation irregularly and appears fibrillar in midspermatids (inset). At the posterior pole of the nucleus, an irregularly shaped IF is formed through migration of the two centrioles toward the posterior pole of the nucleus. C: During further development, the AV enlarges and sinks deeply into the anterior portion of the nucleus, while the subacrosomal space widens. D: A small amount of secretion is attached to the proximal centriole within the wide IF. Note the elongated proximal centriole, which is arranged rectangular to the distal centriole. E: Distinct electron-dense lamellae are arranged around the base of the Ax (arrows)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4612307/files/figure.png" .

